<p>Yummy: The TV star couldn't contain her delight as she prepared to pick up her meal</p>

<p>In good company: The make-up artist added fuel to the rumours about her new fashion edit as she was joined by Treasure Evans - Missguided's Senior Creative and Campaign Manager</p>

<p>Pregnancy cravings: After picking up some food at the store, the brunette collected more bags at the drive-thru</p>

<p>On her rumoured edit, a source told MailOnline: 'Charlotte's skyrocketed in popularity over lockdown and since she announced her pregnancy brands have been fighting to sign her up for an exclusive contract.</p>

<p>'Her humour and relatability make her the perfect match for her own collection and her nearly 1 million followers on Instagram are the perfect audience to target. Charlotte loves fashion and is so excited and the prospect of her own line.'</p>

<p>MailOnline has contacted representatives for Charlotte and Missguided for further comment. </p>

<p>Just a few weeks ago, the reality star revealed she's 'over the moon' to be expecting a baby with the rugby league player, 28, and is due to give birth just a week before what would have been her father Les' 90th birthday in February 2021. </p>

<p>Oh baby! The media personality revealed she's expecting her first child with boyfriend Matt Sarsfield last month </p>

<p>The comedian passed away from a heart attack aged just 62 when she was just eight months old. </p>

<p>She told OK! magazine: 'We went for the first scan and my due date is actually the week before, but there's every chance I could give birth on his birthday. What a tribute that would be.'</p>

<p>She added: 'He would've been the best grandfather. It's bittersweet because he would have been here, making everyone laugh.'</p>

<p>Famous face: The reality star revealed her baby is due just a week before what would have been her dad Les's 90th birthday, on February 2, 2021 (pictured in 1992)</p>
